00351 /**
00352  * cvmx_sdl#_dl_axc_map_lut#
00353  *
00354  * These registers program the AxC mapping for the download channels of SDL.
00355  *
00356  * Each SDL basic frame (or chip) contains 64 time slots, and each of these
00357  * 16 regsiters controls which AxC is mapped to each time slot.
00358  *
00359  * _ SDL(0..2)_DL_AXC_LUT(0) controls time slots [TS3, TS2, TS1, TS0] with fields 3-0
00360  * respectively.
00361  *
00362  * _ SDL(0..2)_DL_AXC_LUT(1) controls time slots [TS7, TS6, TS5, TS4] with fields 3-0
00363  * respectively,
00364  *
00365  * _ etc.
00366  *
00367  * Note that each AxC must be mapped to either 2, 4, or 8 time slots,
00368  * depending on whether the bandwidth is 5 MHz, 10 MHz, or 20 MHz,
00369  * respectively.
00370  *
00371  * Consecutive time samples for a given antenna should be assigned to strided time
00372  * slots as follows:
00373  * 5 MHz: TS x and TS x+32.
00374  * 10 MHz: TS x, TS x+16, TS x+32, and TS x+48.
00375  * 20 MHz: TS x, TS x+8, TS x+16, TS x+24, TS x+32, TS x+40, TS x+48, and TS x+56.
00376  */

00383     uint64_t axc3                         : 4;  /**< Chooses which AxC is mapped to this time slot. */
00384     uint64_t reserved_21_23               : 3;
00385     uint64_t enable2                      : 1;  /**< Enables the corresponding time slot to be mapped to an AxC. */
00386     uint64_t axc2                         : 4;  /**< Chooses which AxC is mapped to this time slot. */
00387     uint64_t reserved_13_15               : 3;
00388     uint64_t enable1                      : 1;  /**< Enables the corresponding time slot to be mapped to an AxC. */
00389     uint64_t axc1                         : 4;  /**< Chooses which AxC is mapped to this time slot. */
00390     uint64_t reserved_5_7                 : 3;
00391     uint64_t enable0                      : 1;  /**< Enables the corresponding time slot to be mapped to an AxC. */
00392     uint64_t axc0                         : 4;  /**< Chooses which AxC is mapped to this time slot. */
00393 #else
00394     uint64_t axc0                         : 4;
00395     uint64_t enable0                      : 1;

00743 /**
00744  * cvmx_sdl#_ul_axc_map_lut#
00745  *
00746  * These registers program the AxC mapping for the upload channels of SDL.
00747  *
00748  * Each SDL basic frame (or chip) contains 64 time slots, and each of these
00749  * 16 regsiters controls which AxC is mapped to each time slot.
00750  *
00751  * _ SDL(0..2)_UL_AXC_LUT(0) controls time slots [TS3, TS2, TS1, TS0] with fields 3-0
00752  * respectively.
00753  *
00754  * _ SDL(0..2)_UL_AXC_LUT(1) controls time slots [TS7, TS6, TS5, TS4] with fields 3-0
00755  * respectively,
00756  *
00757  * _ etc.
00758  *
00759  * Note that each AxC must be mapped to either 2, 4, or 8 time slots,
00760  * depending on whether the bandwidth is 5 MHz, 10 MHz, or 20 MHz,
00761  * respectively.
00762  *
00763  * Consecutive time samples for a given antenna should be assigned to strided time
00764  * slots as follows:
00765  * 5 MHz: TS x and TS x+32.
00766  * 10 MHz: TS x, TS x+16, TS x+32, and TS x+48.
00767  * 20 MHz: TS x, TS x+8, TS x+16, TS x+24, TS x+32, TS x+40, TS x+48, and TS x+56.
00768  */
00769 union cvmx_sdlx_ul_axc_map_lutx {
00770     uint64_t u64;
00771     struct cvmx_sdlx_ul_axc_map_lutx_s {
00772 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
00773     uint64_t reserved_29_63               : 35;
00774     uint64_t enable3                      : 1;  /**< Enables the corresponding time slot to be mapped to an AxC. */
00775     uint64_t axc3                         : 4;  /**< Chooses the target AxC for this time slot. */
00776     uint64_t reserved_21_23               : 3;
00777     uint64_t enable2                      : 1;  /**< Enables the corresponding time slot to be mapped to an AxC. */
00778     uint64_t axc2                         : 4;  /**< Chooses the target AxC for this time slot. */
00779     uint64_t reserved_13_15               : 3;
00780     uint64_t enable1                      : 1;  /**< Enables the corresponding time slot to be mapped to an AxC. */
00781     uint64_t axc1                         : 4;  /**< Chooses the target AxC for this time slot. */
00782     uint64_t reserved_5_7                 : 3;
00783     uint64_t enable0                      : 1;  /**< Enables the corresponding time slot to be mapped to an AxC. */
00784     uint64_t axc0                         : 4;  /**< Chooses the target AxC for this time slot. */
00785 #else
00786     uint64_t axc0                         : 4;
00787     uint64_t enable0                      : 1;
00788     uint64_t reserved_5_7                 : 3;
00789     uint64_t axc1                         : 4;
00790     uint64_t enable1                      : 1;
00791     uint64_t reserved_13_15               : 3;
00792     uint64_t axc2                         : 4;
00793     uint64_t enable2                      : 1;
00794     uint64_t reserved_21_23               : 3;
00795     uint64_t axc3                         : 4;
00796     uint64_t enable3                      : 1;
00797     uint64_t reserved_29_63               : 35;
00798 #endif
00799     } s;
